  "body": "This is a sequel to Issue #300 .\r\n\r\nIn order to turbo-geth to be a net-positive for the network, we need to try to support the GetNodeData in any way we can.\r\n\r\nFor the hashes that are not in the `TrieDbState`, we can maintain a fixed-size pipeline that would remember the request for `GetNodeData` (and the peer that has asked), and ask another peer for it (obviously, we should not ask other turbo-geth peers or peer that originated the request), and respond when we get the data, or remove the pending request after a timeout.\r\n\r\nMaintain an LRU cache of hashes to nodes retrieved via proxying.",
